text: Sybra strandi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Stephan von Breuning in 1939.BioLib.cz - Sybra strandi. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. It's 6.5–8 mm long and 2–2.25 mm wide, and its type locality is Madurai, India. It was named in honor of Embrik Strand, in whose Festschrift the species description was written. ==References== strandi Category:Beetles described in 1939 Category:Taxa named by Stephan von Breuning
title: Sybra strandi
